"I prefer enemies that stay dead," Cody grunted, hand diving reflexively into his bag. The dart in his hand when it
came back out flew directly at the face of the kobold zombie, covering the six inches of space between Cody's hand and
the eye socket of the undead monster in the blink of an eye. The zombie gave a strange shudder and collapsed, and Cody
lowered his hand, heart pounding.
